{"Body": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Best player you never signed?</strong></p>\n<p>Paul Gascoigne.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>How do you relax away from the game?</strong></p>\n<p>It&rsquo;s easier for me to relax now, years ago not so much. I love history, reading and watching movies, I just saw Avatar recently. I&rsquo;m quite active away from football and I keep three or four books by my bedside all the time. Reading the &lsquo;Painting of the Sistine Chapel by Michelangelo&rsquo; and Ted Kennedy&rsquo;s book currently.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>How do you motivate your players with them earning large sums of money?</strong></p>\n<p>I think they deserve the money, they earn it. I&rsquo;m straightforward with my players, successful people want to be successful.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>What is your view on friendly internationals?</strong></p>\n<p>I don&rsquo;t think the managers themselves think that they are any use, they never play their full teams! The international calendar is a lot better now than it was before. The international friendly in March is ridiculous with British clubs competing late in European competitions.</p>\n<p><strong>Any up and coming Irish youth players?</strong></p>\n<p>Robert Brady and Conor Devlin a youth team goalkeeper. Shay Given was at United as a kid but his father wanted him to sign for Glasgow Celtic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Best goal you&rsquo;ve ever witnessed for United?</strong></p>\n<p>A Denis Irwin goal at Wimbledon. Great team goal, thirty two passes before the finish. Ryan Giggs&rsquo;s goal against Arsenal galvanised the club-an emotional game and an emotional moment.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Would Mark Hughes be welcome back at Old Trafford?</strong></p>\n<p>Absolutely. One of our great players. Did you know forty one players have played for both United and City? &lsquo;Sparky&rsquo; never played bad in the big games.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Who will retire first, Alex Ferguson or Rya